{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3415551,"name":"Brian Weiss","username":"brianweiss","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/5f9b8f/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-08-14T22:12:14.295Z","cooked":"<p>I’m currently working on implementing a dynamic autonomous routine using Choreo. The goal is to transition between different paths based on the visibility of a note during the match. However, I’m encountering an issue where the robot stops after attempting to transition to a new path, and the simulation crashes.</p>
<p>I’m obtaining this output &amp; error:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">Path1 is done
Error at com.pathplanner.lib.commands.FollowPathCommand.isFinished(FollowPathCommand.java:217): Unhandled exception: java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke "com.pathplanner.lib.path.PathPlannerTrajectory.getTotalTimeSeconds()" because "this.generatedTrajectory" is null
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Here’s the problematic code:</strong></p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">// Function to decide the next path
public void execute() {
    if (currentCommand != null &amp;&amp; currentCommand.isFinished()) {
        // Path1 is done
        System.out.println("Path1 is done");
        path1Completed = true;
        decideNextPath();
    }
}

private void decideNextPath() {
    if (path1Completed) {
        if (DynamicPathPlanner.noteIsVisible()) {
            // Switch to Path3
            currentCommand = RobotContainer.ChoreoAuto(newAutoCaseNote);
        } else {
            // Continue with Path2
            currentCommand = RobotContainer.ChoreoAuto(newAutoCaseNoNote);
        }
        currentCommand.schedule();
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p><strong>RobotContainer.java:</strong></p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public static Command ChoreoAuto(String name) {
    return AutoBuilder.followPath(PathPlannerPath.fromChoreoTrajectory(name));
}
</code></pre>
<p>These paths do in fact exist in Choreo and as a .traj file.</p>
<p>In this scenario , noteIsVisible() returns false.</p>
<p>Thank you for helping.</p>
